ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend ENAS806 for anybody that is interested in solar technology. It is an absolute must-have for this field.
Yes I definitely would recommend this to others.
A great course for introduction of semiconductors and solar cells.
Yes, it's helpful to widen the knowledge
It a very useful and good course. For people who are curious about solar cell technology, this is the course to take.I will recommend it to other students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course material has helped my research directly. Although the materials covered in class are aimed at silicon or III-V solar cells, the theory can be extended to new, emerging photovoltaic systems as well.In addition to the course materials, Professor Lee is happy to take questions outside of the course. He is a valuable resource in learning and thinking about such devices.
Learned a lot of new knowledge that I have never contacted before. Quite useful!
It helps broaden my knowledge of semiconductor microelectronics to the field outside logic application.
